item.title: NullPointerException
item.dc:creator: @LeScape LeScape
item.description:
@LeScape wrote:

It’s simple, look at the lines specified and see what’s up with it. What it does, if it’s something like loading a .cfg file then you have a “error” in your .cfg. It doesn’t show up on the compiler, but it errrors when reading it because you don’t have all of the data. Example: there are 15 numbers of data for item.cfg on each item, along with a description and item ID. If you only have 14 lines of number data, when it tries to load the .cfg it errors.
